## ✅ Day/Night Mode Scenarios

### 1. Toggle Visibility & Basic Toggle Behavior

- [ ] Day/Night mode toggle is **visible** in the main UI
- [ ] Toggle is **enabled** (clickable) in default state
- [ ] Clicking toggle switches from **Day → Night** theme
- [ ] Clicking again switches from **Night → Day** theme
- [ ] No console errors or layout breaks on toggle

---

### 2. Visual Changes (Main Page)

- [ ] Background color changes according to selected mode
- [ ] Text remains **readable** in both Day and Night modes
- [ ] Buttons and inputs remain clearly visible and usable
- [ ] Links and hover states are visible in both modes
- [ ] No elements remain in “old” theme (mixed styles)

---

### 3. Chat Area & Messages

- [ ] Chat background updates to match selected theme
- [ ] User and bot messages stay readable (no low-contrast text)
- [ ] Timestamps, avatars, and system messages remain visible
- [ ] Code blocks / formatted responses are legible in both modes

---

### 4. Persistence After Page Refresh

- [ ] Switch to **Night** mode, then refresh page
- [ ] Night mode remains active after refresh
- [ ] Switch back to **Day** mode, refresh again
- [ ] Day mode remains active after refresh
- [ ] No “flash” of wrong theme during load (if possible to check)

---

### 5. Persistence Across Navigation (If Multiple Pages)

- [ ] Enable Night mode on main chat page
- [ ] Navigate to another in-scope page (e.g., settings / info)
- [ ] Theme is still **Night** on the new page
- [ ] Navigate back to chat page → theme still consistent

---

### 6. New Session Behavior

- [ ] Close tab/browser completely
- [ ] Reopen Askeal AI
- [ ] Confirm behavior matches expected product decision:
  - Either theme persists between sessions **or**
  - Mode resets to default and this is documented
- [ ] No inconsistent behavior across browsers

---

### 7. Interaction With Other Features

- [ ] Day/Night toggle works correctly while chat is active
- [ ] File upload dialog / modals respect theme colors
- [ ] Error banners and notifications are readable in both modes
- [ ] “Recent howls” and footer section follow the theme correctly

---

### 8. Edge Cases & Stress

- [ ] Rapid toggling (click toggle several times quickly) does not crash UI
- [ ] Toggle during ongoing LLM response does not break streaming
- [ ] Toggle while scrolling long conversation keeps text readable
- [ ] No significant performance lag when switching themes

---

### 9. Cross-Browser Checks

- [ ] Chrome: all above scenarios pass
- [ ] Firefox: theme toggle and persistence behave the same
- [ ] Safari (if available): no visual regressions or missing styles

